NAME
    ldg_libpath - locate a dynamical library.

SYNOPSIS
    int ldg_libpath( char *path, WORD *gl);

PARAMETERS
            ldg : LDG descriptor returned by ldg_exec() function.
         global : global array used by AES functions,
         return : 1 if the library is located, 0 else.

DESCRIPTION
    This  function  returns  the  effective  location  of  a  library.
    ldg_open() uses it  to locate  library. Before the  call, path  is
    filled with the  name of the  library to locate.  At return,  path
    contains the full location of the library. path should pointed  on
    a sufficienly large buffer. This function quite is different of 
    ldg_getpath() which uses to know the exact path of the library 
    inside it.

   
SEE ALSO
    ldg_open(), ldg_getpath().

